Date:  16/9/1957
Source:  NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page:  95(3):293
Edition:
Quote:  Seed sown on paddock at Rimu, Southland in 1880. English origin? Seed from this sown on `Glenelg' Mossburn and in 1887 this property bought by Mr George Chewings. First considerable quantity of seed harvested in 1890. Within the next few years, when local farmers were producing larger quantities Chewings on holiday in the North Island advised runholders to try his fescue seed. Inquiries received in Invercargill for `Chewings' fescue.'
Notes:  [R. Mason]

