Source:  NZ Pocket Oxford Dictionary
Author:
Vol / Page:  123
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Chewings fescue</i> NZ kind of grass used for pasture and lawns.  [Charles <i>Chewings</i> seedsman]  W3 often cap C [after Charles Chewings [dagger sign] 1937 Australian scientist]: a perennial pasture and turf grass (<i>Festuca rubra commutata</i>) closely related to red fescue but producing a closer firmer sod and tolerating partial shade.
